  <main id="main" class="wrap">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="heroShell">
        <div class="heroInner">
          <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Privacy • minimal data • evidence discipline</div>
          <h1>Privacy policy.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Noetfield collects only what is needed to route intakes and respond. We do not sell personal information.
            Keep submissions non-confidential (no credentials, no internal security details, no private client data).
          </p>

          <div class="pillRow" aria-label="Highlights">
            <div class="pill"><strong>Purpose-limited</strong></div>
            <div class="pill"><strong>No selling data</strong></div>
            <div class="pill"><strong>Non-confidential intakes</strong></div>
            <div class="pill"><strong>Request ID tracking</strong></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid">
      <!-- MAIN -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="hd">
          <h2>Policy</h2>
          <p>Effective date and scope.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bd">
          <div class="section" id="scope">
            <div class="sectionTitle">1) Scope</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              This policy applies to the Noetfield website and its pages, including Gate and Partners lanes.
              Some pages include forms that send submissions to a form processing provider (e.g., Formspree) as configured on the page.
            </p>

            <div class="kv" aria-label="Policy metadata">
              <div class="k">Effective</div>
              <div class="v"><span id="effectiveDate">2025-12-13</span></div>

              <div class="k">Owner</div>
              <div class="v">Noetfield Systems Inc.</div>

              <div class="k">Contact</div>
              <div class="v"><a href="/contact/">/contact/</a></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="what-we-collect">
            <div class="sectionTitle">2) What we collect</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">We collect data you provide, plus minimal technical telemetry needed for basic site operation.</p>

            <ul class="list">
              <li>
                <strong>Form submissions:</strong> information you enter into a form (e.g., name, email, role, organization, notes, links).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Request IDs:</strong> some flows generate a <code>request_id</code> used to track an intake across pages
                (for example: <code>/status/?rid=...</code> or <code>/thanks/?rid=...</code>).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Basic technical data:</strong> standard web server logs (e.g., IP address, user agent, timestamps, requested path) for security and reliability.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Local storage:</strong> the site may store non-sensitive keys in your browser (e.g., last <code>rid</code>, lane/track) to improve continuity.
              </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="box">
              <strong>Do not submit confidential information.</strong> Forms are designed for links and summaries only, not uploads of sensitive documents or credentials.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="how-we-use">
            <div class="sectionTitle">3) How we use information</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">We use your information to route, respond, and improve site reliability.</p>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Routing:</strong> categorize by track/lane (e.g., Gate vs Partners; integration vs delivery) and prioritize follow-up.</li>
              <li><strong>Response:</strong> reply to your inquiry, request clarifications, or schedule next steps.</li>
              <li><strong>Quality:</strong> identify broken links, form failures, or UX issues.</li>
              <li><strong>Security:</strong> protect the site against abuse and spam.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="sharing">
            <div class="sectionTitle">4) Sharing and service providers</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              We may share data with service providers that help operate the site (for example: form processing, email delivery, analytics if enabled).
              Providers process data on our behalf to deliver the requested function.
            </p>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Form processing:</strong> a provider configured in the form’s <code>action</code> URL receives submissions.</li>
              <li><strong>Email delivery:</strong> if enabled, submissions may be forwarded to designated inboxes for response.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="box">
              <strong>No selling of personal data.</strong> We do not sell your personal information to third parties.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="cookies">
            <div class="sectionTitle">5) Cookies and local storage</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              We may use cookies or local storage for basic functionality (navigation state, routing continuity, request ID continuity).
              You can clear storage in your browser settings; some flows may become less convenient.
            </p>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Functional:</strong> remember an <code>rid</code> or track so you can continue an intake.</li>
              <li><strong>Security:</strong> basic anti-spam measures (where enabled).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="retention">
            <div class="sectionTitle">6) Data retention</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              We retain information only as long as necessary for the purposes described above, unless a longer retention is required for compliance,
              dispute resolution, or security investigation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="your-rights">
            <div class="sectionTitle">7) Your choices and rights</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              You can request access, correction, or deletion of your submitted personal information, subject to legal and operational limits.
              Use the contact page and include the relevant <code>request_id</code> if available.
            </p>

            <div class="box">
              <strong>Tip:</strong> If you submitted an intake, include your <code>Request ID</code> so we can locate it quickly.
              Use <a href="/contact/">/contact/</a>.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="security">
            <div class="sectionTitle">8) Security</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              We use reasonable measures to protect information. No system is perfectly secure; please avoid sending sensitive information through web forms.
            </p>

            <ul class="list">
              <li>Minimized collection and purpose-limited usage.</li>
              <li>Anti-spam measures may be added over time.</li>
              <li>Operational access limited to what is needed to respond and route.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="changes">
            <div class="sectionTitle">9) Changes</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              We may update this policy to reflect changes in site functionality. The effective date will be updated on this page.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="section" id="contact">
            <div class="sectionTitle">10) Contact</div>
            <p class="sectionDesc">
              Questions about this policy: use <a href="/contact/">/contact/</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

